# nmonLocalLLM -- Cline rules

Loaded on every Cline task in this repo. Keep rules terse; deep context lives in `architecture/`, `bug_reports/`, and `nmon Documentation/`.

## Project shape

- Textual TUI for NVIDIA GPU + local LLM server monitoring.
- **src-layout Python package.** Source lives in `src/nmon/`, NOT at the repo root.
- Entry point: `nmon.main:run` (installed as console script `nmon`).
- Python 3.11+. `mypy --strict`, `ruff` (line-length 88), `pytest` with `pythonpath=["src"]`.
- Subpackages:
  - `src/nmon/gpu/` -- NVIDIA NVML via `nvidia-ml-py` (`monitor.py`, `protocol.py`)
  - `src/nmon/llm/` -- Ollama-style HTTP polling via `httpx` (`monitor.py`, `protocol.py`)
  - `src/nmon/storage/ring_buffer.py` -- fixed-size time-series store
  - `src/nmon/ui/` -- Textual `App`, `dashboard.py`, tabs (`llm_tab`, `power_tab`, `temp_tab`), `alert_bar.py`

## Import rule (src-layout trap)

- Tests and runtime code import as `from nmon.<submodule> import ...`, never `from src.nmon.<...>`. `pyproject.toml` sets `pythonpath=["src"]` for pytest; at runtime the console-script entry makes `nmon` importable directly.
- If you see a Cline suggestion with `from src.nmon...`, that's wrong -- strip the `src.` prefix.

## Hard rules (repo-wide)

- **No emojis** in source, docs, commits, CLI output, or TUI text.
- **Full type annotations on new code.** `mypy --strict` must pass.
- **No defensive programming.** Only validate at true boundaries (NVML calls, HTTP responses, subprocess output). Don't wrap trusted internal calls in try/except.
- **No backwards-compat shims.** No `# removed` comments, no dead re-exports, no `_unused_` renames -- delete.
- **Comments are rare.** Only write one when the WHY is non-obvious.
- **No `--no-verify` on commits.**

## Textual (in `src/nmon/ui/`)

- **Never block the event loop.** NVML calls, disk I/O, and `httpx` sync calls go through `asyncio.to_thread` / `run_in_executor`.
- Use `reactive(...)` for state that drives the DOM. Don't `.query_one(...).update(...)` for things the reactive system should own.
- Test Textual components with `Pilot` (pytest-asyncio). Don't try to unit-test widgets without the app loop.

## NVML (in `src/nmon/gpu/`)

- `nvmlInit()` runs ONCE at app startup, `nvmlShutdown()` at teardown. Don't wrap per-sample.
- NVML device handles are process-local; cache in one place. Don't share across processes.
- `NVMLError` must be caught only where the UI needs a fallback value. Elsewhere, let it propagate.

## HTTP (in `src/nmon/llm/`)

- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with an explicit `timeout=`. Never `httpx.get()` / `requests.*` in event-loop code.
- Treat the LLM server as flaky: timeouts, 5xx, and empty bodies are normal. Surface them through the monitor's state -- don't let exceptions crash the TUI.

## Storage (in `src/nmon/storage/`)

- `ring_buffer.py` is the single source of truth for time-series history. Don't stash rolling history inside widgets.
- Ring-buffer capacity is fixed at construction. Don't grow at runtime.

## Testing

- Tests live in `tests/`, mirroring `src/nmon/` where possible.
- `pytest-asyncio` for async tests, `pytest-mock` (`mocker` fixture) for patching.
- When fixing a bug that's named in `bug_reports/SUMMARY.md`, add a regression test AND update the bug report entry in the same commit.
- Don't mock NVML with a bare `MagicMock()` -- the pipeline's `bug_reports/` history shows that drifts from real binding behavior. Use `pytest-mock` to patch specific functions (`nvmlDeviceGetHandleByIndex`, `nvmlDeviceGetPowerUsage`, etc.) with realistic return types.

## Debug workflow (analysis + debug artifacts exist in this repo)

`architecture/INTERFACES.md`, `architecture/DATA_FLOW.md`, `architecture/xref_index.md`, `architecture/callgraph.md`, `bug_reports/SUMMARY.md`, `test_gaps/GAP_REPORT.md` are generated by `C:\Coding\LocalLLM_Pipeline\Common\ArchPipeline.py`. At the start of any debugging task, @-mention the relevant subset.

Full workflow: see `C:\Coding\LocalLLM_Pipeline\Common\Documentation\Cline.md`.

If artifacts look stale (file mtimes older than recent source edits), regenerate:

```
cd C:\Coding\WorkFolder\nmonLocalLLM
python C:\Coding\LocalLLM_Pipeline\Common\ArchPipeline.py analysis
python C:\Coding\LocalLLM_Pipeline\Common\ArchPipeline.py debug --target-dir src/nmon
```

## Workflow

- **Plan Mode first** for any non-trivial change. Switch to Act Mode only after the plan is confirmed.
- Read `architecture/interfaces/src/nmon/<file>.iface.md` before editing that file.
- For risky / irreversible actions (destructive git, deleting files, closing issues), confirm with the user first -- even in Act Mode.

## Git

- Commit subjects short and declarative. "why" in the body only if non-obvious.
- New commits over `--amend`.
- No `Co-Authored-By` credits unless the user requests them.
- Never force-push main.
